Senior Slaphead's Twitch Channel

OVERVIEW

My previous career run was deleted from Twitch by their new Amazonian Overlords. Sadly I had only created a few random highlights and that is all that remains:

Spaceplane Intro, Cloudy Landing, Munar Shipyard & Orbital Station, Kethane Rig Deployment, Spaceplane Cargo Recovery

You can follow my more recent Dark Multiplayer exploits on YouTube.

Edited September 12, 2016 by Senior Slaphead
YouTube link added

Second stream is up.

This episode: bit of tinkering in the VAB, launch of new crew shuttle, return of lander from Mun, rendezvous with shuttle, deadly re-entry of shuttle. science acquired, profit!

Incidentally the lander is usually capable of deadly re-entry itself but I knew I was going to be testing the shuttle anyway, so I left the lander's shield at home. The lander has been left in orbit for future use.

Next stream probably later this evening.

Today's (Tuesday) stream will involve lifting a station core, a solar array and some escape pods. Starting 20:00 GMT.

UPDATE: Had to abandon this one due to an issue with an associated mod (Universal Storage). The station will probably have to wait until this is updated.

Edited April 30, 2014 by Senior Slaphead

And.... back.

During the hiatus I've been re-learning how to build and fly outsized spaceplanes and I now have a new one in service: The 'Delta V'. This uses the B9 pack with traditional jet engines and a rocket rather than sabres or rapiers, mostly because I didn't like the resulting weight distribution with the latter. It can carry 50+ tons into low orbit. Naturally I'm still using all the realism mods, including FAR. Under my new austerity rules this is the only vehicle I'll be using to lift stuff from Kerbin.

On the Mun there is a new tanker for ferrying fuel from my Kethane mine to the Shipyard, allowing me to move four times as much fuel in one go. The first of several Greenhouses lifted by spaceplane are en route to the Munar station and bases to make the TAC life support self-sustaining. The atomic propulsion sections used in these Munar transits will form part of my next interplanetary mission to be assembled at the station. I'm operating under the additional restriction that only basic parts should be buildable on the Mun... creating greenhouse plants from Munar ore would have been preposterous.

I also did a landing on Moho that produced plenty of science but has left two kerbals stranded with a disabled craft (I ran out of fuel 100 meters from touchdown, broke the legs and toppled over). In theory I could probably save them with some KAS jiggery-pokery and many, many trips to ferry fuel up to the interplanetary stage... if I can secure enough alcohol it will happen.

The spare lander orbiting Kerbin was refuelled and sent out to Minmus to mop up the last of the biomes. Having completed two landings and topped up on Kethane it will return to Kerbin in the next stream. A few thousand more science should complete the tech tree at which point I shall re-install KSP Interstellar to extend the challenge.

I should be streaming later today and/or this evening. Will post a 30 minute warning.

Stream starts in the next half hour. I plan on doing the Minmus return, landing of the first Greenhouse, plus spaceplane launch and assembly of the second Greenhouse. A friend is also playing KSP tonight so the commentary will include our (on topic) ksp discussions. Happy to also take questions from the stream although please bear with us as we may be distracted.
